HEADWORD: Ethnography
<hw>Eth*nog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ nation
+ <ets>-graphy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ethnographie</ets>.]</ety> <def>That
branch of knowledge which has for its subject the characteristics of the
human family, developing the details with which ethnology as a
comparative science deals; descriptive ethnology. See
<er>Ethnology</er>.</def></p>

